ce:section.ce:para:
In addition to the XPS peak fitting analysis, the method of D parameter has been employed to identify the hybridization states or coordination numbers (sp2 and sp3) of carbon atoms in the as-prepared CQDs [40]. In particular, the value of the D parameter was calculated, for both the samples, as the distance between the most positive maximum and most negative minimum of the first derivative C KVV spectrum, as shown in Fig. 5
                        a–b. The obtained results (Table 2
                        ) highlight that both the as-produced CQDs exhibit a graphene-like carbon configuration (for literature, D ≈ 13 eV, [40]).
